Vendored diago notice
---------------------

The vendored `third_party/diago` source is copyright (c) 2024 Emir Aganovic
and is licensed under the Mozilla Public License 2.0. Its full license text is
kept in `third_party/diago/LICENSE.txt`.

Audio assets
------------

Asterisk English voice prompts under `assets/sounds/` are Copyright Allison
Smith (see `assets/sounds/CREDITS-*`) and licensed under Creative Commons
Attribution-ShareAlike (CC BY-SA). The full license text for each bundle is in:

- `assets/sounds/LICENSE-asterisk-core-en-1.4.27`
- `assets/sounds/LICENSE-asterisk-core-en-1.6.1`
- `assets/sounds/LICENSE-asterisk-extra-en-1.5.2`

When you distribute those WAV files, include the matching LICENSE and CREDITS
files. Do not modify the prompt recordings without complying with ShareAlike.

Music on hold is not bundled in this repository. Deployments must supply their
own royalty-cleared WAV files under `assets/moh/` (see `assets/moh/README.md`).

G.729 codec note
----------------

The Go package `github.com/hunydev/g729` is MIT-licensed, but the G.729 algorithm
may be patent-protected in some jurisdictions. Evaluate patent obligations
separately from this software copyright license.
